data.description:
Seller offering to pay up to $10,000 towards buyer closing costs or rate buy down with acceptable offer! Welcome home to this solid brick ranch-style home on an extra large lot (nearly a half acre) with extra parking and plenty of space to store your boat or RV/camper. This well maintained home offers three bedrooms and two full baths--both bathrooms have separate shower and vanity areas for ease of sharing. The master bathroom has an open vanity area with two separate areas for showing and throne room. In the living area, there are two family rooms; the den offers a beautiful brick gas fireplace. The kitchen has appliances that are just a few years old, the French door style refrigerator has water & ice in the door & two lower drawers; the gas stove will make the cook happy. Read MORE There is a large kitchen island (on wheels) with bar seating and storage (stored in the garage). There are beautiful glass double doors to the back patio from the den just off the kitchen, and a gas stub outside for your BBQ grill--so you'll never run out of fuel while grilling dinner! Speaking of gas, for efficiency there is a gas water heater (2 years old), and gas furnace (HVAC is 3 years old). 
The windows were replaced 2012; Hurricane pegs in place for ease of covering; Beautiful double doors with clear glass storm doors and hidden half screen option for those lovely spring and fall days. The big garage has plenty of shelves to stay organized plus there are two out buildings for extra storage. Out back there is a big patio and fully fenced backyard with plenty of space to relax or play. Mature trees offer shade and host plenty of song birds. This home has a durable and beautiful brick exterior with low maintenance vinyl trim with gutters and downspouts. There is a lawn pump and sprinkler system. The roof is 9 years old and in good condition. 
This home is not on a thru-street with less traffic and is conveniently located in Niceville, just a short distance from schools, shopping, parks (Children's park; Meigs Park, Softball complex; dog park), restaurants and military bases.
